\begin_layout Subsection
Elimination of Dominated Strategies
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A 
\series bold
dominated strategy
\series default
 is something that is worse than an alternative that a player can play,
 
\series bold
regardless
\series default
 of how the other players play.
 A reasonable and rational player should not play dominated strategy.
 One can iteratively eliminate dominated strategies (which can't be played),
 in order to find the best response strategy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As a strategy is undominated iff it is a best-response strategy, the order
 of the elimination doesn't matter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In mixed strategies it is much more difficult to recognize domination, compared
 to pure strategies, as there are more possibilities to be considered.
\end_layout

